  "text": "In the absence of severe cardiac defect heterotaxy and intestinal malrotation usually manifest by non-specific symptoms in neonates and infants such as cry and vomiting. For that reason, the diagnosis may be delayed until patient present with intestinal obstruction. [CITATION_1] If congenital heart defect is present, birth and post-natal care must be planed in order to provide immediate specialized treatment. [CITATION_2] The prenatal diagnosis of heterotaxy in presence of a cardiac defect must lead to the assessment of the abdominal situs. Genetic counseling is recommended.",
